{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

  <p>A Search bar is best used to give a user the ability to search for something and then display any relevant search results.</p>

  <h4>Layout</h4>

  <p>A Search bar can be used in most layouts. It has no maximum width other than the boundaries of a container or any grid columns it is placed in.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='medium') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-layout.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component usage" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Content</h4>

  <p>A Search bar includes text within a form field that can indicate how wide or narrow a search can be. If the placeholder text is written to be <strong>generic</strong> (<em>Enter a search term</em>), a user might expect to search an entire website. If the placeholder text is written to be <strong>specific</strong> (<em>Search all resources</em>), a user might expect to search an individual page.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-placeholder-text.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component placeholder text options" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

{% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

  <h4>Form field</h4>

  <p>When a user selects the form field to input text via cursor or keyboard, the placeholder text will disappear, the form field will have focus, and a blinking cursor will be visible. When a user starts typing, the text styling will change.</p>

  <!-- Temporary Info alert until web component release -->
  <p style="background-color: #e7f1fa; border-top: 2px solid #2b9af3; padding: 16px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;">Visit the <a href="https://ux.redhat.com/components/form/" target="_blank">Form</a> component page to learn more about form fields.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-form-field.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component styling changes" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Typeahead</h4>

  <p>In some cases, when a user inputs text, a short list of suggested queries will appear below the form field.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-typeahead.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component typeahead" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Errors</h4>

  <p>If focus is moved from the form field to the button, an error icon and text <strong>will not</strong> be displayed. However, if a user tries to perform an <em>empty search</em>, or a search without any text in the form field, an error icon and text <strong>will be</strong> displayed.</p>

  <!-- Temporary Info alert until web component release -->
  <p style="background-color: #e7f1fa; border-top: 2px solid #2b9af3; padding: 16px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;">Visit the <a href="https://ux.redhat.com/components/form/" target="_blank">Form</a> component page to learn more about form field errors.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-errors.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component form field errors" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

{% call components.section("Interaction states") -%}

  <!-- Temporary Info alert until web component release -->
  <p style="background-color: #e7f1fa; border-top: 2px solid #2b9af3; padding: 16px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;">Visit the <a href="https://ux.redhat.com/components/form/" target="_blank">Form</a> or <a href="https://ux.redhat.com/components/button/" target="_blank">Button</a> component pages to learn more about interaction states.</p>

  <h4>Link</h4>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-interaction-states-link.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component interaction state, link" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Hover</h4>

  <p>A subtle blue line appears at the bottom of the form field indicating it is selectable.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-interaction-states-hover.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component interaction state, hover" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Focus</h4>

  <p>When the focus is moved to the form field by a user pressing the Tab key, the placeholder text will disappear and a blinking cursor will be visible. When the focus is moved away, the placeholder text will be visible again.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-interaction-states-focus.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component interaction state, focus" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Active</h4>

  <p>When the focus is moved to the form field by a user selecting it with their cursor, the placeholder text will disappear and a blinking cursor will be visible. When the focus is moved away, the placeholder text will be visible again.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-interaction-states-active.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component interaction state, active" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Tab order</h4>

  <p>When the Tab key is pressed repeatedly, the focus will highlight the form field first and then the button. A user can move the focus from the form field to the button without an error icon and text being displayed.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/search-bar/search-bar-tab-order.svg' | url }}" alt="Search bar component tab order" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
  {%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

